In this article, President Trump welcomes President Niinistö of Finland to the Oval Office. They discuss the strong relationship between the two countries and the trade surplus that Finland has against the United States. President Niinistö expresses his thoughts and sympathy for the people affected by Hurricane Harvey in Texas, and President Trump thanks him for the support. President Trump announces that he will be traveling to Texas the next day to assess the situation and praises the coordination and spirit of the people in handling the disaster. He also mentions the possibility of visiting Louisiana depending on the storm's path. President Trump mentions that they have had Cabinet meetings and are working with Congress to ensure coordination and financial assistance for the affected areas. The article concludes with President Trump and President Niinistö preparing to move to the East Room for another event.